text:
Yet can't handle a logic puzzle that gives her the position of 2 chess pieces, doesn't shoot to kill or stun monsters in her way when running from X, didn't board up windows, leading to more zombies to interfer, didn't disable any zombies by shooting one of their knees apart, left behind items, including purposely leaving ammo for Leon that he couldn't even get, frequently got lost, struggled with tracing the circuit paths to hack, and didn't shoot or grenade the gas pipe before the croc chewed through it and killed her. I think she should give herself time-limits to solve puzzles and longer limits to generally make progress, and if she gets stuck, accept some help from chat.

She made me realize why Devs hold your hand so much in so many modern games, it's because of gamers like Gura, who struggle so much with basic things like navigation, logic, stealth, any prudence, and how to even start a puzzle.
The game even offered to help her with aiming, yet she was too prideful to accept.

I think she should play games on easy mode, then after beating them, play them again on harder & harder difficulties, getting more playtime & streaming out of a game, and not getting so overwhelmed.

And after beating a game on it's hardest difficulty, she and or the chat, can set up challenges, like beat the game in a certain time, or ignore certain weapons, or whatever.

She's cute and randomly says funny & hilarious things, but as a gamer, her F-ups & delays can be so frustrating & disappointing to witness.

I'm always so pumped to see other people enjoy the games I love.
Thank you for streaming this Gura and I'm looking forward to you beating it, playing more Resident Evil games, and more horror games! (I love em). □
